    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">FREE PEOPLE:<br />
<br />
Basically this is a simple Ring-bound Ranger deck.  Nothing big.  You have the Gondorian Ranger to keep Minions in skirmishes Roaming.  Faramir and Aragorn (I know he is un-bound) are tanks...<br />
I chose Aragorn, RotN because he is a Ranger and you can make him a possible Defender +3 if need be.  Which I haven&#39;t seen yet.<br />
You can bid pretty much whatever you want.  You will remove 2 at the start of the game for play Faramir and Gondorian Ranger.<br />
ALSO - this FP is meant to run hard and beat down opponents Shadow.  Nazgul are the only thing slowing these bad boys down for the time being.<br />
<br />
SHADOW:<br />
There are a lot of minions.  This ensure you can&#39;t have a &quot;bad&quot; hand.  You will almost always draw up a minion.  Some minions allow you to take control of sites, though some are way circumstantial.  Don&#39;t worry about it.  You can at any time drop 3-4 minions on a Fellowship and crush them.<br />
The Mumak is something new I wanted to try...so far it&#39;s pretty good.  I might even add more or add in the other Mumak.<br />
<br />
SITES:<br />
They suck...but so do most of the sites...play to you and you opponents disadvantage - which shows how good your deck really is.<br />
<br />
BID:<br />
Yeah...bid whatever...2 are gone at the start of the game...just don&#39;t over bid by any means.<br />
<br />
Good luck... </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
